r would provide growth opportunity in china where there is rapid modernization driven by the need to increase grain productivity and increase food qualitychris pultz a kellner merger investors fund portfolio manager who leads the firms merger arbitrage investing characterized the syngenta deal as a vital strategic move that could help fill chinas need to feed the countrys growing population by upgrading farming techniques crop yield and food safetychem china offered  for each syngenta share a  premium to tuesday the deal endorsed by syngentas board includes an additional special dividend of  swiss francs approximately  per share if the deal is finalized both companies said they expect the transaction to close by the end of the yearchemchina is headquartered in beijing and is not a publicly traded firm syngenta is based in basel its swisslisted shares closed  higher at  swiss francs wednesday after retreating from higher gains earlier in the trading sessionthe deal represents the latest consolidation of the chemical and agribusiness sector following the  billion merger deal dow chemical and dupont announced in decemberst louisbased rival monsanto wooed syngenta with a roughly  billion merger deal last year but dropped the bid when the swiss company rejected the sweetened offer it was unclear wednesday whether monsanto would propose a new offerchemchinas success in landing the deal marks the latest crossborder corporate foray by the company and its chairman chemchina last year acquired italian tire maker pirelli in a  billion transactionnotable proposed acquisitions so far this year by chinabased firms include haier groups  billion purchase of general electrics appliance business and dalian wanda groups  billion deal for legendary entertainmentusa todaychinas wanda buys us film studio legendary for  billionren jianxian and john ramsay syngentas ceo issued statements saying their deal would further expand syngentas presence in emerging markets including china they also predicted the transaction would win regulatory approvals however pultz predicted the us will have to weigh in as to whether this is a matter of national securityfederal regulators could seek oversight review in part because syngenta operates two business divisions in the us seeds and crop protection and also operates a regional headquarters in greensboro nc the company reported  billion in  north america sales including the us a  oneyear declineled by the department of the treasury the committee on foreign investment in the united states conducts national security reviews of transactions that could result in control of a us business by a foreign person or companyusa todaysmithfield shareholders ok b sale to china firmthe agency did not block another major food deal involving china the  billion takeover of virginiabased pork production giant smithfield foods by chinas shuanghui international meat processing companyhowever royal philips nv in january said it had terminated a  billion sale of its lighting components and automotive lighting business to a consortium led by chinese company go scale capital because the us agency did not approve regulatory clearance  connecttweet  linkedincommentemailmoreread or share this story httpusatlyxtat china national chemical corp chemchina to buy stakes in adama home about us contact us careers competition home news description china national chemical corp chemchina to buy stakes in adama china adama agricultural solutions ltd is a major producer and distributor of crop protection products the company is  owned by china national agrochemical corp which is a subsidiary of china national chemical corp chemchina adama agricultural solutions ltd  is expected to merge with sanonda an agriculture chemicals producing company which is owned by chemchina this agreement of an international entity to combine with publicly traded company in china was possible after the consent of china securities regulatory commission csrc the shareholders of